  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "バベルは、プレイヤーが考古学者インディアナ・ボーグナインを操作し、バビロンの空中庭園を探し求めるプラットフォームパズルゲームです。庭園への唯一の道は、有名なバベルの塔の恐ろしい64階を通り抜けることにあります。\n\n主人公は、宝物を集めながら聖書に登場する構造物のさまざまな部屋から脱出しなければなりません。各部屋は別々のパズルであり、主な目的はL字型のブロックを拾って積み上げ、階段や橋を作って出口の扉に到達することです。これらの部屋では、プレイヤーがブロックを拾う回数は限られています。また、プレイヤーは飛んでいるコウモリやゴーレム、司祭の警備員などの roaming enemies に触れないように注意しなければなりません。探検者が行き詰まったり、一連の誤った行動によってレベルが解けなくなった場合、ボタンを押すことで主人公を殺し、部屋をリセットすることができます。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Mystery Tower, previously known as The Tower of Babel (Babel no Tou) or just Babel, is an action puzzle game. The game consists of 64 \"floors\" or puzzles that involve the positioning of many L-shaped blocks. You must manipulate them to create stairs so you can reach the exit of each floor. Some floors are sealed, and you must collect crystal balls to escape. There are items to collect for bonus points, and a small number of enemies to avoid.\n\nThe game was a Japan-exclusive title up until its release on the Nintendo Switch Online service, finally receiving its current overseas title.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "In the beginning, an archaeologist and explorer known as Indiana Borgnine is in search of the fabled Hanging Gardens of Babylon. After reading some lost scriptures, he determines that the only way to see them is to travel to the very top of the 64-story Tower of Babel. Upon reaching the Tower, he discovers that the only way to access the floors above him are to solve some challenging puzzles involving loose L-shaped blocks that he finds throughout the Tower. To his great surprise, the blocks are capable of balancing very well on top of one another, in order to form staircases.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
    },
